name: The prison of traumas
description:
It took me a depression to understand that I was in prison. The labyrinth to get out of it is long, full of detours, but so rich in learning that in the end, I could thank to have been imprisoned for so long and to have made this depressive peak. 
The work of cellular reprogamming is laborious, takes time, I chose to erase everything and start over. This requires accepting the ups and downs, not fighting, but welcoming. 
Even if sometimes you feel like you are stuck, in a dead end. Look more carefully at the situation, change your angle of view, take a step back and you will see that it opens doors to more beautiful worlds.
